'Lead(II) oxide', also called lead monoxide, is the inorganic compound with the
molecular formula PbO. PbO occurs in two polymorphs, one having a tetragonal
crystal structure and the other having an orthorhombic crystal structure. Modern
applications for PbO are firstly in lead-based industrial glass and industrial
ceramics, including computer components.
